<dl id="n09063i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09063i">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09063i"> 63(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Lemuel</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">There was a great flat stone over that small parcel of the rector&apos;s freehold, which the family held by a tenure, not of lives, but of deaths, renewable for ever. So that my uncle, who was a man of an anxious temperament, had little trouble in satisfying himself of the meerings and identity of this narrow tenement; to which <mark>Lemuel</mark> Mattocks, the sexton, led him as straight and confidently as he could have done to the communion-table. <small> J. Sheridan Le Fanu, <a name="HBC1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#HBC1"><cite title="source">The House by the Churchyard</cite></a> (1899) 4</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
